    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large strong nets intended to protect construction workers, circus acrobats, or others from falling to the ground from heights, or to protect people on the ground from falling debris or construction materials.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047033/Princeton WordNet Lexical Database (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>大而強韌的網子，用以保護建築工人、馬戲特技演員或其他人，以免他們自高處落至地面，或保護地面上的人不被掉落的碎片或建築材料砸到。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Großes, starkes Netz zur Absicherung von Bauarbeitern, Zirkusakrobaten und anderen gegen Abstürze aus großer Höhe oder um Personen auf dem Boden vor herabstürzenden Baumaterialien zu sichern.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
